  "prompt": "If a person weighs 150 pounds, how much should their arm weigh?",
  "response": "The weight of a person's arm can vary depending on several factors such as overall body composition and muscle mass. However, a general estimate often cited in medical literature suggests that an arm accounts for approximately 5-6% of total body weight.\n\nGiven this approximation, if a person weighs 150 pounds:\n- 5% of 150 pounds is 7.5 pounds.\n- 6% of 150 pounds is 9 pounds.\n\nTherefore, the person's arm would likely weigh between 7.5 and 9 pounds.",
